1
00:00:00,640 --> 00:00:02,399
The Cozy English.

2
00:00:02,399 --> 00:00:04,260
Learn English slowly.

3
00:00:05,044 --> 00:00:07,960
Welcome to the Cozy English.

4
00:00:07,880 --> 00:00:11,999
I'm Emma, and I'm so glad you're here with us again today.

5
00:00:11,999 --> 00:00:13,160
And I'm Daniel.

6
00:00:13,255 --> 00:00:17,075
It's always nice to have this quiet moment with you.

7
00:00:17,075 --> 00:00:19,975
We hope your day's been gentle so far.

8
00:00:19,895 --> 00:00:24,215
Every week, we sit here together with our tea,

9
00:00:24,134 --> 00:00:31,100
our thoughts, and a little bit of English practice to talk about life and growth.

10
00:00:31,259 --> 00:00:36,299
And today's topic is something I think we all feel at some point.

11
00:00:36,620 --> 00:00:39,820
Nothing changes if nothing changes.

12
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:42,460
That phrase really makes me think.

13
00:00:42,745 --> 00:00:46,904
It sounds simple, but it's kind of uncomfortable too,

14
00:00:46,824 --> 00:00:49,945
because it means if I keep doing the same things,

15
00:00:49,945 --> 00:00:52,225
I'll keep living the same story.

16
00:00:52,225 --> 00:00:53,464
Exactly.

17
00:00:53,464 --> 00:00:56,505
It's that moment when you look around your life,

18
00:00:56,490 --> 00:01:00,169
your job, your habits, your routines,

19
00:01:00,250 --> 00:01:04,809
and realize that everything feels the same.

20
00:01:05,370 --> 00:01:09,130
Not bad, just quietly repeating.

21
00:01:10,075 --> 00:01:15,855
Days blend into each other, and you start to wonder, is this it?

22
00:01:15,855 --> 00:01:17,514
I know that feeling.

23
00:01:17,515 --> 00:01:25,114
It's not like you're unhappy, but there's this tiny voice in your head saying, maybe something should change.

24
00:01:25,190 --> 00:01:26,209
Right.

25
00:01:26,209 --> 00:01:28,230
But most of us wait.

26
00:01:28,230 --> 00:01:35,029
We tell ourselves, I'll start when I have more time, or maybe next month.

27
00:01:35,350 --> 00:01:43,524
But that next month becomes next year, and slowly we stop believing that things can be different.

28
00:01:43,445 --> 00:01:46,884
So the real problem isn't that change is impossible.

29
00:01:46,805 --> 00:01:49,725
It's that we get used to staying the same.

30
00:01:49,725 --> 00:01:50,724
Yes.

31
00:01:50,965 --> 00:01:57,160
Change asks for energy, courage, and sometimes a little discomfort.

32
00:01:57,560 --> 00:02:01,240
But staying stuck also costs us something.

33
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:06,100
Our excitement, our curiosity, our growth.

34
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:07,719
I think about this a lot.

35
00:02:07,985 --> 00:02:12,545
Sometimes I want to learn something new or try a different routine,

36
00:02:12,465 --> 00:02:15,944
but then my brain says, what if you fail?

37
00:02:15,944 --> 00:02:18,905
Or what if nothing changes anyway?

38
00:02:18,905 --> 00:02:21,185
That's such a human thought.

39
00:02:21,330 --> 00:02:24,130
We all want results right away.

40
00:02:24,130 --> 00:02:27,649
But change usually begins quietly.

41
00:02:27,810 --> 00:02:32,130
It starts the moment you decide to do something different,

42
00:02:32,290 --> 00:02:36,530
even if it's small, like waking up ten minutes earlier,

43
00:02:36,735 --> 00:02:39,493
saying no to one habit,

44
00:02:39,493 --> 00:02:45,006
or finally taking the first step towards something that scares you.

45
00:02:44,915 --> 00:02:52,200
So that's the real turning point, when you stop waiting and start doing, even just a little.

46
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:53,359
Exactly.

47
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:58,240
And that moment, even if it's tiny, is powerful.

48
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:01,239
Because once you take it, you're no longer
